        <section id="why">
            <h1>Why Strapless?</h1>
            <p>Strapless isn't a CSS micro/mini/nano-framework. It's a CSS boilerplate. It just makes your plain HTML look good.</p>
            <p>With only six semantic CSS classes to worry about (action, reaction, success, failure, info, warning), Strapless frees you from the overprescriptive cruft of frameworks. Use the grid you like. Snag a dropdown menu that works for your project, not the one we picked and named for you. You were probably going to do that <em>anyway</em>, right?</p>
            <p>Strapless aims to let you work how you want, building your project from the ground up, instead of chiseling it out of a we-know-better block of marble.</p>
            <p>Basically, Strapless makes your HTML look like this page. Try it out now by changing the base color. Then, download that color's CSS file and use it to start building&mdash; from the ground up.</p>
        </section>

